# Normalize line endings for all text files to LF in the repository,
# regardless of core.autocrlf or the OS/editor that last touched them.
# Added 2026-07-17 after a full OS reinstall caused a 92-file CRLF/LF
# mismatch (old machine's committed LF content vs new machine's CRLF
# working-tree files, surfaced because core.autocrlf=false on the rebuilt
# machine). This also prevents a repeat of the bybit_sim_run.bat silent-
# failure issue, which was caused by a file being saved with LF-only line
# endings on a .bat file that Windows cmd.exe needs as CRLF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows batch files specifically need CRLF to run reliably in cmd.exe —
# override the general eol=lf rule above for this one extension.
*.bat text eol=crlf